# Rule Sync — Cursor ↔ Claude Code

When adding or modifying a rule in `.cursor/rules/` or Cursor User Rules, ask:

> "Would you like this rule also mirrored to Claude Code?"

## If yes

1. **Output for `~/.claude/rules/`**: Provide a fenced code block with the full rule content as a plain `.md` file, ready to save to `~/.claude/rules/[rule-name].md`.

2. **If it's a new top-level rule category** (not just an addition to an existing rule), also note that `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` should be updated with a pointer to the new file, following the existing section format:
   ```markdown
   ## N. Rule Title
   See detailed instructions in `~/.claude/rules/[rule-name].md` (auto-loaded).
   - Key bullet summary
   ```

## What goes where

| Rule type | `.cursor/rules/` | Cursor User Rules |
|-----------|-----------------|-------------------|
| Detailed workflow/reference (research, memory, session) | ✓ Full content | — |
| Short hard constraint (em dash, modification policy, orphan words) | ✓ Full content | ✓ Condensed |

## Parity locations

- Cursor workspace rules: `/Users/mygirleatsmayo/Desktop/Dev/.cursor/rules/`
- Claude Code rules: `~/.claude/rules/`
- Claude Code index: `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md`
- Cursor global (User Rules): Cursor Settings → Rules for AI (manual, cloud-stored)
